      "metadata": [
        
        {
                        "name": "13.B.2 Outlays on fixed assets serving environmental protection in research-development activity",
                      
                        "goal": "Goal 13. Climate action",
                      
                        "priority": "Introduction of innovative technologies for the use of available energy sources",
                      
                        "definition": "Gross fixed capital formation for environmental protection in research and development.",
                      
                        "unit": "thousands, PLN",
                      
                        "dimensions": "total",
                      
                        "methodology": "Gross fixed capital formation – expenditure that increases the value of fixed assets and expenditure incurred for the repair of fixed assets and the increase in intangible assets.Investments on environmental protection – expenditure on creation or increase of fixed assets serving environmental protection. They can be expressed:1) in monetary terms, as investment expenditures incurred for environmental protection activities,2) in tangible form (effects), as environmental protection devices or technical equipment used for environmental protection purposes. Those may be end-of-pipe equipment or integrated technologies.Research and development (R&D) - research and experimental development (R&D) comprise creative and systematic work undertaken in order to increase the stock of knowledge - including knowledge of humankind, culture and society - and to devise new applications of available knowledge.The five criteria for identifying R&D:• novel - to be aimed at new findings,• creative - to be based on original, not obvious, concepts and hypotheses,• uncertain - to be uncertain about the final outcome and the cost, including time allocation,• systematic - to be conducted in a planned way (with identified the purpose of the R&D project and the sources of funding),• transferable and/or reproducible - to lead to results that could be possibly reproduced.Research and development includes:1. scientific researcha)	- basic researchb)	- applied research (industrial research)2. experimental development",
                      
                        "source": "Statistics Poland / Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development / Chief Inspectorate of Environmental Protection / Ministry of Climate and Environment",
                      
                        "availability": "Annual data, since 2010",
                      
